> Craving tacos, but short on time? Meet chicken tinga—the quickest, simplest way to turn a quick weeknight dinner into a flavor fiesta. This smoky Mexican dish is traditionally made with tomato, chipotle pepper, and adobo sauce, but there are tons of ways to spin it! Our version features chicken breast strips in a saucy blend of tomato paste and fajita spice. The filling is stuffed into soft flour tortillas and topped with creamy, lime-y corn salad. If you've got some on hand, be sure to serve with chips and salsa, and most of all, good company. It takes two to tinga!

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Drain @corn kernels{13.4%oz}.

== Chicken Tinga ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken to hot pan in a single layer; cook,
stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} to pan. Stir in scallion whites, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and @fajita spice blend{3/4%tsp}. Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/4 cup @water{}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Cook, stirring, until chicken
is coated in sauce, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Corn Salad ==

While chicken cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine corn,
lime zest, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @fajita spice blend{1/4%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, a squeeze of lime
juice, and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like. Season with
salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave
until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates. Fill with chicken filling
and as much corn salad as you like. Garnish with scallion
greens. Serve with any remaining corn salad and lime
wedges on the side.